                        <handDesc hands="2">
                            <handNote scope="sole" script="unknown">
                                <p>The last page is written in Latin.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kålund</name> (<bibl>
                                        <ref type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">Katalog</ref>
                                        <biblScope unit="volume">I</biblScope>
                                        <biblScope unit="pages">18</biblScope>
                                    </bibl>) attribute the last handwritten page (p. 269) to <name
                                        type="person" key="JonOla003">Jón Ólafsson from
                                        Grunnavík</name>. The hand, however, most likely belongs to
                                    his brother, <name type="person" key="ErlOla001">Erlendur
                                        Ólafsson</name>.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>Later added marginalia in places.</p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding>
                                <p>Half-binding with spine and corners of marbled leather, possibly
                                    from <date notBefore="1785" notAfter="1799">the end of the
                                        eighteenth century</date>. The boards are covered in
                                    marbled paper <!-- bakkemarmor -->. Size of binding: <dimensions
                                        type="binding" unit="mm">
                                        <height unit="mm">336</height>
                                        <width unit="mm">225</width>
                                        <depth unit="mm">22</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <p>The spine is divided into six panels by seven line segments; the
                                    title was embossed in the second section from the top. The Foot
                                    of the spine carries the initials of the <name type="org"
                                        key="KB">Copenhagen University Library</name>: B.U.H. </p>
                                <p>In all likelihood this is the first binding of the manuscript,
                                    made when the volume entered the collection. On pp. 47-48 it can
                                    be noticed that the pages were cut after the marginalia was
                                    written.</p>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
